  <p>
    The solution in grounding grid analysis depends directly on the grid discretization. The smaller the segment, the more faithful the representation of reality.<br><br>In this study, I simulated a 100x100m grid with 10x10m grids with different segment sizes. The graph shows that reducing the segment size leads to a more uniform voltage distribution that is closer to the real value.
